A Lefkovitch model updates the stage-structured population each time step by matrix multiplication, so the population after one decade is given by $N_{1} = L N_{0}$. Using the given $L$ and $N_{0}$,
$$
N_{1} = \begin{pmatrix} 0  0  4.2 \\ 0.25  0.50  0 \\ 0  0.15  0.85 \end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix} 2000 \\ 500 \\ 150 \end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
0\cdot 2000 + 0\cdot 500 + 4.2\cdot 150 \\
0.25\cdot 2000 + 0.50\cdot 500 + 0\cdot 150 \\
0\cdot 2000 + 0.15\cdot 500 + 0.85\cdot 150
\end{pmatrix}
= \begin{pmatrix}
630 \\ 750 \\ 202.5
\end{pmatrix}.
$$
The projected number of adult trees (the third component) after one decade is $202.5$, which rounded to three significant figures is $203$.
